<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio" id="Jump-Squats">Jump Squats</h3>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Jump squats are a high-intensity, dynamic exercise that combines the strength of traditional squats with an explosive jump. This <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/34168689/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">plyometric</a> movement primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves while engaging the core for stability and balance.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Performing <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC4974862/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">jump squats</a> regularly builds lower body strength and enhances explosive power. They are particularly effective for improving vertical jump height and sprint speed, which benefits athletic performance. The intense nature of this exercise also increases <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7377236/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">calorie burn</a>, making it ideal for weight loss and overall fitness.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC9748292/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">Jump squats</a> improve mobility, especially in the hips, and enhance balance and coordination. These functional benefits make them valuable for athletic activities and everyday movements. Additionally, when performed with proper form, they promote joint stability.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">As a compound exercise, jump squats work multiple muscle groups simultaneously while boosting cardiovascular fitness. This efficiency makes them an excellent addition to any full-body workout routine.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo vimeo-custom wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
