<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">How To Do</h4>



<ol type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Stand with feet shoulder-width apart.</li>



<li>Lower into a squat position, bringing your hips and knees just past 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Jump explosively upward.</li>



<li>Land softly back into the squat position, returning to the ground with the balls of your feet first.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Tips&nbsp;</h4>



<ul type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Keep your chest up and knees behind your toes during the squat.</li>



<li>Use your arms to gain momentum during the jump</li>



<li>Land with soft knees to absorb impact and protect your joints.</li>



<li>Keep your core engaged throughout the movement.</li>
</ul>



