<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio" id="Jumping-Lunges">Jumping Lunges</h3>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Jumping lunges are a high-intensity <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/33401532/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">plyometric</a> exercise that combines strength and cardio in a single explosive movement. This exercise primarily targets the quadriceps, hamstrings, glutes, and calves while engaging the core for <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36395192/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">balance</a> and stability.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Regularly incorporating jumping lunges into your routine builds lower-body strength and enhances cardiovascular fitness. Their dynamic nature improves power, agility, and overall functional fitness.&nbsp;</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Jumping lunges also improve balance and coordination as you alternate legs in a controlled yet explosive motion. This makes them ideal for enhancing athletic performance and refining lower-body mechanics to maximize <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/35437711/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">stability</a>.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Their high-intensity nature boosts <a href="https://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC7377236/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">calorie burn</a> and supports weight loss, adding metabolic benefits to their strength-building effects. As a versatile exercise requiring no equipment, jumping lunges are perfect for home workouts or as part of a full-body training program.</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo vimeo-custom wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
