</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Jumping Lunge Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">How To Do</h4>



<ol type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Begin in a lunge position with your right foot forward and left foot back, both knees bent at 90 degrees.</li>



<li>Push through both feet to jump explosively into the air.</li>



<li>Switch legs mid-air, landing softly with your left foot forward and right foot back in a lunge position.</li>



<li>Repeat the movement continuously, alternating legs with each jump.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Tips</h4>



<ul type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Keep your chest upright and core engaged throughout the exercise.</li>



<li>Land softly to reduce the impact on your joints.</li>



<li>Ensure your front knee stays aligned over your ankle to avoid strain.</li>



<li>Start slow if you&#8217;re new to plyometric exercises, and gradually increase speed as you build strength.</li>
</ul>



