<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">How To Do</h4>



<ol type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Start by standing with your feet hip-width apart.</li>



<li>Begin jogging in place, focusing on kicking your heels up towards your buttocks.</li>



<li>Keep your thighs relatively still, with most of the movement occurring from the knee down.</li>



<li>Pump your arms as you would while running to increase the intensity.</li>



<li>Maintain a quick, rhythmic pace throughout the exercise.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Tips</h4>



<ul type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Keep your upper body straight and core engaged throughout the movement.</li>



<li>Land softly on the balls of your feet to reduce impact.</li>



<li>Aim to touch your buttocks with your heels on each repetition.</li>



<li>Start at a slower pace and gradually increase speed as you build coordination.</li>



<li>Use your arms to maintain balance and increase overall calorie burn.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



