<h3 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio" id="Plank-Jacks">Plank Jacks</h3>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Plank jacks are a dynamic exercise that fuses core strengthening with cardiovascular intensity, offering a comprehensive full-body workout. Plank jacks target the rectus abdominis, obliques, and transverse abdominis, while also engaging the shoulders, chest, triceps, and legs.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">The benefits of plank jacks are extensive, making them a valuable addition to any fitness routine. They improve core stability and cardiovascular fitness, promoting endurance and calorie burn. Their high-intensity nature makes them particularly effective for weight loss and boosting metabolic rate.</p>



<p class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">This exercise is excellent for building strength in the core and <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/39100938/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">upper body</a> while providing a cardio challenge. Plank jacks contribute to better posture by strengthening stabilizing muscles, enhancing functional fitness and coordination.&nbsp;</p>



<figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-vimeo wp-block-embed-vimeo wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio vimeo-custom"><div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper">
<iframe loading="lazy" title="Plank Jacks" src="https://player.vimeo.com/video/982307230?dnt=1&amp;app_id=122963" width="500" height="281" frameborder="0" allow="autoplay; fullscreen; picture-in-picture; clipboard-write"></iframe>
</div><figcaption class="wp-element-caption">Plank Jack Guide. Video: Aliaksandr Makatserchyk</figcaption></figure>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">How To Do</h4>



<ol type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Start in a high plank position with your hands directly under your shoulders and feet together.</li>



<li>Keeping your core tight and body in a straight line, jump your feet out to the sides, wider than hip-width apart.</li>



<li>Immediately jump your feet back together to the starting position.</li>



<li>Continue this in-and-out jumping motion while maintaining a stable plank position.</li>
</ol>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Tips</h4>



<ul type="video" class="wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">
<li>Keep your body in a straight line from head to heels throughout the exercise.</li>



<li>Engage your core muscles to maintain stability and prevent your hips from sagging.</li>



<li>Breathe steadily, exhaling as you jump your feet out and inhaling as you bring them back together.</li>



<li>Start with smaller jumps and gradually increase the width as you build strength and coordination.</li>



<li>If the full plank is too challenging, modify by performing the exercise on your forearms or knees.</li>
</ul>



<h4 class="wp-block-heading wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio">Optimal Sets And Reps</h4>



